snippet.textDisplay: This was so brave of you to share. I can't say I 100% understand where you're coming from and you probably won't end up seeing this but my heart goes out to you and the other individuals affected by all the losses you've been experiencing. I'm so sorry you've been going through this and I really hope 2020 gets better for you. I know that might not entirely matter to you right now but I'm at least glad to hear you have good supports in place and things to keep you busy. You already know to process your feelings but just remember that it's okay to take as much time as you need to heal after all of this. That's a crazy amount of tragedy and suffering to go through and I sincerely hope everything will look up soon but also that you know that it's okay to not be okay. ❤ Love you Jeffree and thank you for all of your hard work, dedication, and for inspiring me even in some of your darkest times. You are beautiful and I wish all the best for you and every one else involved in all of this. I know you said you have a thick skin but if you ever needed a reminder that you are strong and can make it through this - I and so many other people believe in you and know that you can. You are so lovely and I love that you continue to be yourself, live authentically and share your truth. Also in case you also needed to hear that you didn't owe us an explanation and that I'm thankful you gave one regardless then I hope me saying that can make you remember those things if you ever end up reading this. 💖💕😘
